title: For Sale:  Colt Cavalry SAA .45 W/Colt
postcontent: This is a 7 ½” Colt SAA in .45 Colt Caliber. Made in 1876, this pistol was originally sold to the US Military as an “Cavalry” SAA. It was not accepted by the Military Inspectors, and was sent back to Colt. Colt re-worked the pistol, and then sent it to J.P Moores Co in New York for resale on the Civilian Market. The pistol comes with a Colt factory letter that shows the shipment in 1876. The pistol still has a 7 ½” barrel, and the original wooden grips, there is a faint Military Inspector’s marking on the butt of the right grip. The pistol has the Colt Patent Dates, as well as a “US” marking on the left side of the receiver, it also has the # “3351” stamped in that area. The pistol has Colt’s Hartford address on top of the barrel.
